A 21-year-old student has found a way of allowing Facebook users to encode pictures with secret messages.

Owen Campbell-Moore, a computer science student at Oxford University, has created a browser extension that allows people to share secret messages on the social networking site.

Secretbook allows anyone with access to Google Chrome to hide 140 character long messages in JPEG images uploaded to Facebook and these messages can only be unlocked using a personal password.

