As a result, Mr Campbell-Moore had to copy the sites recompression algorithm so that the encoded message is automatically compressed meaning that it does not change when recompressed by Facebook.

Mr Campbell-Moore accepts that the technology could be used by terrorists but he believes that they would not use his method of steganography as it is not entirely secure.

When Wired.com approached Facebook a spokesperson declined to comment on Secretbook.

